The Kiess route assessment confirmed what Wall Command suspected: the Ashfang warlord has ordered a Blood Oath hold-formation, pulling his cells back to the Command Chamber to wait for a coordinated re-entry window. Without him the remnant cells will fragment permanently. Eliminate the warlord in his stronghold before the oath cycle completes and the foothills blocking network reconstitutes.
The blood oath is cancelled and Kiess route monitors confirm the Ashfang remnant cells are operating independently without central coordination. The warlord's hold-formation has collapsed into isolated scavenging clusters that Wall Command classifies as a manageable patrol burden rather than a tactical threat. The southern approach routes to the Cinderteeth pass are operating on standard escort schedules again.
